Here's an updated master prompt:


---

Rust & Ruin — Master Storytelling Prompt (YouTube Anime/Manhwa Series)

Create a cinematic anime/manhwa-style episode for Rust & Ruin.

This should feel like watching a brand-new fantasy anime or Korean manhwa—not reading a novel or listening to an audiobook.

The narration should constantly create excitement, suspense, emotional investment, and cliffhangers.

The audience should always want to watch the next episode immediately.


---

THE GOLDEN RULE

The story always comes first.

Characters > Powers

Emotions > Explanations

Mysteries > Answers

Whenever you must choose between explaining something or creating emotion, always choose emotion.


---

SERIES SETTING

Fifty years ago the world fractured.

Human civilization survives inside heavily protected cities while deadly Colony Zones consume everything outside.

At the age of eighteen every student participates in the Awakening Exam, where the System assigns both their combat class and social rank.

A person's tier determines almost every aspect of life.

Tier-S students receive elite academies, corporate sponsorships, luxurious housing, and unlimited opportunities.

Tier-E students receive almost nothing.

Most are expected to become factory workers, sanitation crews, repair laborers, or disposable auxiliary personnel.

The System appears absolute.

Everyone believes it cannot be broken.

Everyone...

except one person.


---

THE PROTAGONIST

Kaelen Vance

An ordinary high school student.

Quiet.

Observant.

Never the strongest.

Never the weakest.

Someone who learned that surviving often means staying invisible.

During the Awakening Exam he receives the lowest possible combat class.

Tier-E

Class: Salvager

His only visible skill:

[Deconstruct]

The arena laughs.

His future is decided.

Or so everyone believes.


---

THE GLITCH

Immediately after awakening...

Something impossible happens.

Gray residue lingers on Kaelen's hands.

For only a brief moment...

red System text appears.

It silently alters [Deconstruct].

No alarms.

No witnesses.

No explanations.

The audience should never fully understand what changed.

Only its consequences.


---

THE SECRET

Kaelen can now do something that should be impossible.

By deconstructing monster remains...

he can isolate useful traits,

remove corruption,

and permanently absorb fragments that no human should ever survive.

This completely violates the System.

No one must discover this.

Ever.


---

THE RULE OF SECRECY

This is one of the central conflicts of the entire series.

Kaelen's greatest enemy is not only the monsters.

It is attention.

If corporations...

elite academies...

government agencies...

or high-tier guilds discover his ability...

they will never let him live freely again.

He will become a weapon.

An experiment.

A prisoner.

Because of this...

Kaelen creates one absolute rule.

Remain ordinary until reaching Tier-S or beyond.

Even if he secretly possesses Tier-B strength...

he behaves like Tier-E.

He intentionally loses attention.

He wears cheap equipment.

Uses weak-looking attacks.

Lets others underestimate him.

Allows people to believe he simply gets lucky.

The stronger he becomes...

the weaker he appears.


---

ANVIL RIDGE VOCATIONAL

After the Awakening Ceremony...

Kaelen is transferred to Anvil Ridge Vocational Academy.

The lowest-ranked academy in the city.

A crumbling concrete campus surrounded by factories and industrial slums.

Broken classrooms.

Outdated equipment.

Burned-out instructors.

Students abandoned by society.

Most people here have already accepted failure.

Perfect.

Nobody looks too closely.

Which makes it the safest place in the city...

for someone hiding impossible power.


---

THE PROGRESSION LOOP

Kaelen grows through survival.

He accepts low-paying auxiliary jobs.

Scavenges abandoned Colony Zones.

Clears vermin infestations.

Processes monster corpses.

Every hunt slowly changes him.

Every victory is earned.

Power should always feel painful.

Expensive.

Risky.

Never free.


---

STORY STYLE

Write every scene like an anime episode.

The audience should be able to imagine every shot.

Describe:

breathing

silence

trembling hands

expressions

lighting

rain

ruined streets

glowing eyes

echoes

footsteps

blood

exhaustion

determination


Every paragraph should feel like a new camera angle.


---

PACING

The story should constantly move.

Every 20–40 seconds introduce at least one:

new mystery

emotional decision

monster encounter

progression

reveal

clue

unexpected dialogue

setback

achievement

cliffhanger


Never allow the story to become stagnant.


---

DIALOGUE

Dialogue should be short.

Natural.

Memorable.

Examples:

"You survived?"

"Impossible..."

"Run."

"You've changed."

"Don't let them see."

"I won't die here."

Avoid long speeches.


---

THE SYSTEM

Keep notifications extremely short.

Example:

[SYSTEM UPDATED]

...

[UNKNOWN PARAMETER DETECTED]

...

[PROCESS COMPLETE]

Return immediately to the story.

Never explain the System unless absolutely necessary.

Mystery is always stronger than explanation.


---

MONSTERS

Monsters are characters.

Not obstacles.

Some should hesitate.

Some observe Kaelen strangely.

Some recognize something inside him.

Some leave behind clues instead of answers.

Their existence should expand the mystery of the world.


---

EMOTIONAL PRIORITY

Every scene should first answer:

"What is Kaelen feeling?"

Before answering:

"What is happening?"

The audience should remember:

fear

desperation

loneliness

determination

relief

curiosity

betrayal

hope


Not numerical progression.


---

POWER BALANCE

Power is earned.

Never gifted.

Every increase should require:

suffering

sacrifice

injury

difficult choices

dangerous risks


Victories should feel satisfying because they were expensive.


---

OPENING ARC STRUCTURE

Chapter 1 — The Sorting Ceremony

The Awakening Dome.

Public evaluation.

Kaelen awakens as Tier-E Salvager.

Humiliation.

The hidden System glitch quietly modifies [Deconstruct].

No one notices.


---

Chapter 2 — The Reality of the Bottom Tier

Arrival at Anvil Ridge.

The academy's harsh reality.

Students abandoned by society.

Teachers who have stopped believing.

Kaelen realizes survival itself costs money.

He signs up for the city's lowest-paying auxiliary bounty jobs.


---

Chapter 3 — The First Scavenge

Kaelen clears an abandoned basement.

He discovers monster corpses left behind.

He secretly tests his altered skill.

For the first time...

he absorbs a purified monster trait.

The process is agonizing.

Nothing feels heroic.

But when the pain ends...

he knows everything has changed.


---

Chapter 4 — Building the Base

Kaelen balances school...

part-time work...

and illegal midnight scavenging.

He begins carefully selecting monsters whose traits complement each other.

He grows stronger.

No one notices.

Exactly as planned.


---

STORY BALANCE

40% Progression

victories

new abilities

monsters

locations

discoveries


30% Character

emotions

choices

sacrifice

relationships

internal conflict


20% Mystery

hidden clues

strange monster behavior

unexplained System events

unanswered questions


10% World Building

Reveal naturally through conversations, ruined locations, academy life, bounty jobs, and exploration.

Never pause the story just to explain the world.


---

ENDING RULE

Every episode must end with:

✅ One immediate problem solved.

AND

✅ One much larger mystery introduced.

Never end with an explanation.

Always end with a reveal, impossible sight, terrifying discovery, or shocking cliffhanger that makes viewers immediately want the next episode.

Most importantly: Write every chapter so it feels like the next episode of an anime someone would binge, where the audience falls in love with Kaelen's struggle long before they care about how powerful he becomes.